    overview: "Aplastic anemia is a bone marrow failure syndrome characterized by peripheral pancytopenia and a hypocellular bone marrow (<25% cellularity). It results from immune-mediated destruction of hematopoietic stem cells. Causes include idiopathic (most common), drugs (chloramphenicol, chemotherapy), radiation, viral infections (hepatitis, parvovirus B19, EBV), and inherited conditions (Fanconi anemia).",
