    clinicalRelevance: "Severe aplastic anemia: absolute neutrophil count <500/μL, platelets <20,000/μL, reticulocytes <1% (corrected). Must be differentiated from MDS (which has a hypercellular marrow with dysplasia) and hairy cell leukemia (which causes a 'dry tap' with hypocellular marrow).",
