    overview: "Chronic myelogenous leukemia (CML) is a myeloproliferative neoplasm characterized by the Philadelphia chromosome t(9;22)(q34;q11.2), which creates the BCR-ABL1 fusion gene. This constitutively active tyrosine kinase drives uncontrolled granulocyte proliferation. CML progresses through chronic phase, accelerated phase, and blast crisis.",
