    clinicalPearls: ["LOW LAP score distinguishes CML from leukemoid reaction (HIGH LAP)", "Basophilia is a characteristic finding of CML—not seen in leukemoid reaction", "BCR-ABL1 RT-PCR is the most sensitive method for monitoring molecular response to TKI therapy"],
    examPitfalls: ["Philadelphia chromosome is found in ~95% of CML but also in 25% of adult ALL", "LAP score is LOW in CML but HIGH in leukemoid reaction, PV, and infection", "CML blast crisis can be myeloid OR lymphoid—flow cytometry determines lineage"],
    faqJson: [{ question: "What is the Philadelphia chromosome?", answer: "A reciprocal translocation t(9;22) creating the BCR-ABL1 fusion gene with constitutive tyrosine kinase activity, the defining abnormality of CML." }, { question: "How is CML monitored?", answer: "BCR-ABL1 transcript levels by quantitative RT-PCR. Major molecular response is defined as ≥3 log reduction (BCR-ABL1/ABL1 ≤0.1% on International Scale)." }]
